A(x)+B(x) \mod P(x)
\operatorname{GF}(2^4)
P(x)=x^4+x+1
A(x)=x^2+1, B(x)=x^3+x^2+1
A(x)=x^2+1, B(x)=x+1
p
1+1\equiv 0 \pmod 2
\begin{align} &(x^2+1)+(x^3+x^2+1) \\=&(0x^3+1x^2+0x+1)+(1x^3+1x^2+0x+1) \\=& (0+1)x^3+(1+1)x^2+(0+0)x+(1+1) \\=& 1x^3+0x^2+0x+0 \\=& x^3 \end{align}
GF(2^4)
x^4=-x-1=x+1
 (x^2+1)+(x^3+x^2+1)=x^3 + 2x^2+2=x^3 
